title: Lion Youth Socks
description:
Socks developed from Edward Kemeys’ Lion, 1893, from the Art Institute of Chicago’s collection.

We would be "lion" if we did not think these sock were prrrfect! Our socks are inspired by the stately lions designed by Edward Kemeys (American, 1843–1907) that guard the museum’s entrance.  Cotton blend. 

  • Size: Youth Shoe Size 12-4
  • Materials: 71% Cotton, 15% Polyester, 12% Nylon, 2% Spandex
  • Machine Washable.
